cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper involves the use of deep learning models and functional connectivity analysis to inform diagnoses of Autism Spectrum Disorder, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of fMRI data and atlases for feature extraction and analysis suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the study involves the evaluation of behavioral tests and the potential for democratizing medicine, indicating a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
